### API Keys & Config

| Variable | Source | Used By |
|---|---|---|
| `GOOGLE_API_KEY` | [.env](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/.env) | [rag_engine.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/rag_engine.py) — server-side ingestion (captioning + embedding). **This is the platform's key, NOT the user's.** |
| `MASTER_KEY` | [.env](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/.env) | [encryption.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/encryption.py) — Fernet master key for encrypting/decrypting user BYOK API keys |
| User's BYOK key | SQLite `users.encrypted_api_key` | [llm_gateway.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/llm_gateway.py) — decrypted at call time for chat queries |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Dual-key architecture**: The server uses `GOOGLE_API_KEY` for all ingestion (embedding + captioning), while the user's BYOK key is used only for chat-time LLM calls via [llm_gateway.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/llm_gateway.py). This means ingestion quota is shared across all users on a single server key.

