## 2. Step-by-Step Execution Flows

### Flow A: Document Ingestion (The Build Phase)

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["User clicks Upload<br/>(bot_management.py:80)"] --> B["st.file_uploader returns<br/>UploadedFile (BytesIO)"]
    B --> C["Duplicate check: filename<br/>already in this bot?"]
    C -->|Duplicate| D["st.warning — stop"]
    C -->|New| E["add_document(bot_id, filename)<br/>→ SQLite row, status='pending'"]
    E --> F["file_bytes = uploaded_file.read()"]
    F --> G["ingest_document(file_bytes,<br/>filename, bot_id, doc_id)"]
    G --> H{File extension?}
    H -->|.pdf| I["fitz.open(stream=file_bytes)<br/>→ 2x zoom pixmaps<br/>→ JPG per page"]
    H -->|.docx| J["Document(BytesIO(bytes))<br/>→ paragraphs → Pillow<br/>text images → JPG per page"]
    H -->|other| K["ValueError raised"]
    I --> L["For each page image:"]
    J --> L
    L --> M["_generate_page_caption(img)<br/>Gemini Flash Vision API call"]
    M --> N["_embed_text(caption)<br/>Gemini Embedding API call"]
    N --> O["collection.upsert() to ChromaDB<br/>id: bot{id}_doc{id}_page{n}"]
    O --> P["update_document_status<br/>→ 'processed', page_count"]
    K --> Q["update_document_status<br/>→ 'failed'"]
    M -.->|API error| Q
    N -.->|API error| Q
```

**Detailed step sequence:**

| # | Location | What Happens |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | `bot_management.py:80` | `st.file_uploader` returns an `UploadedFile` (BytesIO-like) object |
| 2 | `bot_management.py:88` | Duplicate check — queries [get_documents_for_bot(bot_id)](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/database.py#204-212) to see if filename exists |
| 3 | `bot_management.py:95` | [add_document(bot_id, filename)](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/database.py#190-202) → inserts SQLite row with `status='pending'`, returns [doc_id](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/database.py#239-247) |
| 4 | `bot_management.py:96` | `file_bytes = uploaded_file.read()` → raw bytes in memory |
| 5 | `rag_engine.py:187` | [_get_page_folder(doc_id)](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/rag_engine.py#56-61) → creates `document_assets/doc_{id}/` directory |
| 6 | `rag_engine.py:188` | [get_chroma_collection()](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/vector_store.py#28-38) → returns singleton ChromaDB collection `chatbot_docs` |
| 7 | `rag_engine.py:196` (PDF) | `fitz.open(stream=file_bytes, filetype="pdf")` → PyMuPDF in-memory document |
| 8 | `rag_engine.py:198-202` | Each page → `get_pixmap(matrix=2x)` → saves as `page_{n}.jpg` to disk |
| 9 | `rag_engine.py:68-115` (DOCX) | `Document(BytesIO(docx_bytes))` → extract paragraphs → wrap to ~40 lines per "page" → render as white-background Pillow images → save as `page_{n}.jpg` |
| 10 | `rag_engine.py:217` | **PER PAGE**: [_generate_page_caption(image_path)](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/rag_engine.py#148-171) — opens image, sends to `gemini-2.5-flash` Vision with extraction prompt → returns verbatim caption |
| 11 | `rag_engine.py:218` | **PER PAGE**: [_embed_text(caption)](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/rag_engine.py#119-132) — calls `genai.embed_content(model="models/gemini-embedding-001")` → returns 768-dim float vector |
| 12 | `rag_engine.py:221-233` | `collection.upsert()` — stores embedding + caption text + metadata (`bot_id`, [doc_id](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/database.py#239-247), `page_num`, `source_image_path`) in ChromaDB |
| 13 | `rag_engine.py:235` | [update_document_status(doc_id, "processed", page_count)](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/database.py#214-229) in SQLite |
| 14 | `bot_management.py:116` | `st.rerun()` refreshes the page to show the updated document list |

> [!WARNING]
> **Rate limit bottleneck**: Steps 10–12 fire **2 API calls per page** (1 Vision + 1 Embedding). A 10-page PDF = 20 API calls in rapid succession. Free-tier Gemini quota is ~5 RPM, which guarantees a `429 RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED` on any document over 2 pages.

---

### Flow B: User Query (The Retrieval Phase)

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["User types message<br/>(chat.py:129)"] --> B["intent_router.classify(query)<br/>→ 'verbatim' | 'quick_qa' | 'external'"]
    B --> C{Intent?}
    C -->|external & level < 2| D["Set escalation=1<br/>Show confirmation UI"]
    D -->|User confirms| E["Set escalation=2<br/>gateway.generate() without docs"]
    D -->|User declines| F["Reset escalation=0<br/>Continue RAG-only"]
    C -->|verbatim / quick_qa| G["query_bot() in rag_engine.py"]
    G --> H["_embed_query(user_query)<br/>Gemini Embedding API"]
    H --> I["collection.query()<br/>Top-3 by cosine similarity<br/>WHERE bot_id = {id}"]
    I --> J["Load page images from<br/>source_image_path on disk"]
    J --> K["Assemble prompt:<br/>SYSTEM_GUARDRAILS +<br/>bot system_prompt +<br/>chat_history (last 3 turns) +<br/>user question"]
    K --> L["gateway.generate(provider,<br/>api_key, prompt, images)<br/>→ User's BYOK key"]
    L --> M["Append citation footnote<br/>→ render answer"]
```

**Detailed step sequence:**

| # | Location | What Happens |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | `chat.py:129` | `st.chat_input` captures user text |
| 2 | `chat.py:136` | [classify(query)](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/intent_router.py#42-64) — keyword scan against `_VERBATIM_KEYWORDS` and `_EXTERNAL_KEYWORDS` |
| 3 | `chat.py:174-177` | If [external](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/views/chat.py#214-245) and escalation < 2 → set escalation=1, return `None` (no answer yet), show confirmation buttons |
| 4 | `chat.py:179-188` | If confirmed external → `gateway.generate()` with system prompt only, no document context |
| 5 | `rag_engine.py:297` | [_embed_query(user_query)](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/rag_engine.py#134-147) — embeds with `task_type="retrieval_query"` using **server's** `GOOGLE_API_KEY` |
| 6 | `rag_engine.py:298-303` | `collection.query(query_embeddings, n_results=3, where={"bot_id": str(bot_id)})` — **bot isolation via metadata filter** |
| 7 | `rag_engine.py:316-322` | Load each retrieved page's image from `source_image_path` metadata via `Image.open()` |
| 8 | `rag_engine.py:339-345` | Build final prompt: `SYSTEM_GUARDRAILS` + `bot_custom_prompt` + last 3 conversation turns + user question |
| 9 | `rag_engine.py:350-355` | `gateway.generate(provider, api_key, prompt, images)` — calls the **user's BYOK key** via the chosen provider |
| 10 | `rag_engine.py:358-360` | Append citation footnote (`Sources checked: Page X of filename.pdf`) |

> [!NOTE]
> **Bot isolation**: Query results are filtered by `bot_id` metadata in ChromaDB (`where={"bot_id": {"$eq": str(bot_id)}}`). This is the sole mechanism preventing data bleed between bots.

---

### Flow C: Document / Bot Deletion

**Single document delete** (`bot_management.py:142-151`):

| # | Location | What Happens |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | `rag_engine.py:252-258` | `collection.delete(where={"$and": [bot_id, doc_id]})` — removes all ChromaDB vectors for this doc |
| 2 | `rag_engine.py:260-262` | `shutil.rmtree(document_assets/doc_{id}/)` — deletes page images from disk |
| 3 | `database.py:231-236` | `DELETE FROM documents WHERE doc_id = ?` — removes SQLite row |

**Full bot delete** (`bot_management.py:174-187`):

| # | Location | What Happens |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | `database.py:239-246` | [get_all_doc_ids_for_bot(bot_id)](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/database.py#239-247) — fetches all doc IDs |
| 2 | `rag_engine.py:265-272` | Loop: [delete_document(bot_id, doc_id)](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/database.py#231-237) for each doc (ChromaDB + filesystem) |
| 3 | `database.py:249-258` | `DELETE FROM bots WHERE bot_id = ?` — SQLite cascade deletes child [documents](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/database.py#204-212) rows |

