## 3. Data Flow & State Management

### Streamlit Session State

State is maintained across Streamlit reruns via `st.session_state`. Here is every key used:

| Key | Set By | Type | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|
| `user_id` | [app.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/app.py) (dev bypass) / [auth.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/views/auth.py) | `int` | Authenticated user's SQLite ID |
| `username` | [app.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/app.py) / [auth.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/views/auth.py) | `str` | Display name |
| [page](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/rag_engine.py#56-61) | Router | `str` | Current page: `"auth"`, `"dashboard"`, `"bot_management"`, `"chat"`, `"settings"` |
| `active_bot_id` | [dashboard.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/views/dashboard.py) | `int` | Currently selected bot for management or chat |
| `api_provider` | [settings.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/views/settings.py) | `str` | `"google"`, `"openai"`, or `"anthropic"` |
| `chat_history_{bot_id}` | [chat.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/views/chat.py) | `list[dict]` | Per-bot message history (`role` + `content`) |
| `escalation_{bot_id}` | [chat.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/views/chat.py) | `int` | Per-bot escalation level: 0/1/2 |
| `doc_deleted_{doc_id}` | [bot_management.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/views/bot_management.py) | `bool` | Transient flag for delete success toast |

### File Storage

| Location | Lifetime | Contents |
|---|---|---|
| `document_assets/doc_{id}/` | Permanent (until doc delete) | `page_1.jpg`, `page_2.jpg`, … — rendered page images at ~144 DPI |
| `chroma_data/` | Permanent (until doc delete) | ChromaDB persistent storage — embeddings, captions, metadata |
| [chatbot.db](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/chatbot.db) | Permanent | SQLite database file |
| [.env](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/.env) | Permanent | `GOOGLE_API_KEY`, `MASTER_KEY` |

> [!NOTE]
> No temporary files are used. `file_bytes` lives in memory only. PyMuPDF opens the PDF from `stream=bytes` (no temp file), and python-docx reads from `BytesIO(bytes)` (no temp file).

### Database Schema (SQLite)

```sql
-- users: authentication + encrypted BYOK key storage
CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id           INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    username          TEXT    UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    password_hash     TEXT    NOT NULL,          -- werkzeug PBKDF2
    encrypted_api_key BLOB,                     -- Fernet AES-256 encrypted
    created_at        TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

-- bots: each user can have multiple bots
CREATE TABLE bots (
    bot_id        INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    user_id       INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES users(user_id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    bot_name      TEXT    NOT NULL,
    system_prompt TEXT    NOT NULL DEFAULT '',
    created_at    TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

-- documents: PDF/DOCX records per bot
CREATE TABLE documents (
    doc_id      INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
    bot_id      INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES bots(bot_id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    filename    TEXT    NOT NULL,
    status      TEXT    NOT NULL DEFAULT 'pending',   -- 'pending' | 'processed' | 'failed'
    page_count  INTEGER,
    uploaded_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);
```

### Vector Store Structure (ChromaDB)

| Field | Value | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Collection name | `chatbot_docs` | — |
| Distance metric | `cosine` | — |
| Node ID format | `bot{bot_id}_doc{doc_id}_page{page_num}` | `bot3_doc7_page2` |
| Embedding | 768-dim float vector | from `gemini-embedding-001` |
| Document (text) | The Vision-generated caption | Full verbatim page description |
| Metadata: `bot_id` | `str(bot_id)` | `"3"` |
| Metadata: [doc_id](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/database.py#239-247) | `str(doc_id)` | `"7"` |
| Metadata: `page_num` | `int` | `2` |
| Metadata: `chunk_index` | `int` (always `0`) | `0` |
| Metadata: `source_filename` | Original filename | `"invoice.pdf"` |
| Metadata: `source_image_path` | Absolute path to JPG | `C:\...\document_assets\doc_7\page_2.jpg` |

