## 4. Known Failure Modes & Exception Handling

### Every Exception Block in the Codebase

| File | Lines | Catches | Action | Risk |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| [bot_management.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/views/bot_management.py#L113-L117) | 113–117 | `Exception` | `st.error()` + `st.code(traceback)` + console print | ✅ Fixed — now surfaces full traceback |
| [bot_management.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/views/bot_management.py#L149-L150) | 149–150 | `Exception` | `st.error(f"Delete failed: {exc}")` | ⚠️ No traceback shown |
| [bot_management.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/views/bot_management.py#L185-L186) | 185–186 | `Exception` | `st.error(f"Delete failed: {exc}")` | ⚠️ No traceback shown |
| [rag_engine.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/rag_engine.py#L238-L242) | 238–242 | `Exception` | Sets doc status to `"failed"`, prints traceback, re-raises as `RuntimeError` | ✅ Fixed — now logs full traceback |
| [chat.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/views/chat.py#L201-L211) | 201–211 | `KeyError`, `RuntimeError`, `Exception` | Returns formatted error string to chat bubble | ✅ Good — includes `traceback.format_exc()` |
| [chat.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/views/chat.py#L233-L239) | 233–239 | `KeyError`, `RuntimeError`, `Exception` | Same as above (escalation path) | ✅ Good |
| [llm_gateway.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/llm_gateway.py#L186-L198) | 186–198 | Generic `Exception` | Pattern-matches error strings for 401/429, re-raises typed errors | ✅ Good |
| [database.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/database.py#L86-L87) | 86–87 | `sqlite3.IntegrityError` | Returns `None` for duplicate username | ✅ Good |
| [encryption.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/encryption.py#L68-L72) | 68–72 | `InvalidToken` | Re-raises as `ValueError` | ✅ Good |
| [settings.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/views/settings.py#L73-L74) | 73–74 | `EnvironmentError` | `st.error()` for missing `MASTER_KEY` | ✅ Good |

### Specific Failure Scenarios

#### What happens if the user uploads an unsupported file?
- `st.file_uploader` on line `bot_management.py:80` restricts to `type=["pdf", "docx"]` — **Streamlit blocks other file types at the widget level**. Even if bypassed, `rag_engine.py:209` raises `ValueError("Unsupported file type")` which is caught and shown.

#### What happens if the Gemini API times out, rejects the model, or hits a rate limit?

| Failure | Where | What Happens |
|---|---|---|
| **Rate limit (429)** during ingestion | [_generate_page_caption()](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/rag_engine.py#148-171) or [_embed_text()](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/rag_engine.py#119-132) | Exception caught at `rag_engine.py:238`, doc status set to `"failed"`, traceback printed, `RuntimeError` bubbles to `bot_management.py:113` → shown in UI |
| **Rate limit (429)** during chat | [query_bot()](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/rag_engine.py#279-363) → `gateway.generate()` | [_handle_error()](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/llm_gateway.py#185-199) in `llm_gateway.py:194` detects "429/rate limit/quota/resource_exhausted" → raises `RuntimeError` → caught at `chat.py:207` → shown as `⚠️ Rate Limit:` message |
| **Invalid API key (401)** during chat | `gateway.generate()` | [_handle_error()](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/llm_gateway.py#185-199) detects "401/unauthorized" → raises `KeyError` → caught at `chat.py:201` → shown as `⚠️ API Key Error:` |
| **Bad model name** | `genai.GenerativeModel(VISION_MODEL)` | The SDK raises an error on `.generate_content()`, caught as generic `Exception` |
| **Network timeout** | Any `genai.*` call | Unhandled by retry logic — crashes into the generic `except Exception` block |

#### What happens if the database is locked or unreachable?
- **No protection**. All [database.py](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/database.py) functions open a fresh `sqlite3.connect()`, execute, and close. There is no:
  - Connection pooling
  - Retry on `sqlite3.OperationalError` (database locked)
  - WAL mode for concurrent reads/writes
  - Transaction timeout configuration
- If two Streamlit sessions try to write simultaneously, SQLite may throw `OperationalError: database is locked`. This exception is **not caught anywhere** and would crash the Streamlit session with a raw error.

### Additional Risks Identified

| Risk | Severity | Details |
|---|---|---|
| **No retry logic on API calls** | 🔴 High | Ingestion makes 2N API calls for N pages with zero backoff. Guaranteed `429` on free tier for any doc > 2 pages. |
| **Dev login bypass is active** | 🟡 Medium | `app.py:57-66` auto-logs in as `dev_admin/admin123`. Auth page is entirely bypassed. Fine for dev, dangerous if deployed. |
| **GOOGLE_API_KEY in .env is committed** | 🔴 High | The [.env](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/.env) file contains a live API key. If [.gitignore](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/.gitignore) doesn't cover [.env](file:///c:/Users/makka/Music/chatbot-project/.env), this key is in version control. |
| **Image paths are absolute in ChromaDB** | 🟡 Medium | `source_image_path` stores full absolute paths like `C:\Users\...`. Moving the project folder breaks all image lookups during query. |
| **No pagination on document list** | 🟢 Low | If a bot has hundreds of documents, `get_documents_for_bot()` loads all at once. |
| **Intent router is keyword-based** | 🟡 Medium | False positives are common. "Explain the table on page 4" triggers `external` instead of `verbatim`. Self-documented as V2 backlog. |
| **`google.generativeai` is deprecated** | 🟡 Medium | Google warns to migrate to `google.genai`. Will stop receiving updates/fixes. |

